      ],
      [
        "Built in 1913 of Carthage Stone , a hard limestone from the Ozarks , as an orphanage and retirement home . Commandeered in 1942 for use by the U.S. military , and used as an Enlisted Men 's Service Club . Then German and Italian prisoners-of-war were held there , still during World War II . The listing was announced as the featured listing in the National Park Service 's weekly list of October 16 , 2009 . Also known as Pythian Castle",
        [
          "/wiki/World_War_II",
          "/wiki/National_Park_Service"
        ]
